3. **Named-let with string args**: Ensure string values are correctly copied across bounces
4. **Named-let with cons args**: `(let loop (lst '(1 2 3)) ...)` — cons chain copied correctly
5. **Multi-param named-let**: `(let loop (a 0 b 1 c 2) ...)` — all bindings preserved
6. **Variadic tail call**: Variadic closure in tail position with TCO bounce
7. **Regular tail call chain**: `(define (f n) (if (zero? n) 0 (g (- n 1))))` + `(define (g n) (if (zero? n) 0 (f (- n 1))))`
8. **Zero-arg closure in tail position**: No env copy needed

